next
  Summary: Offline guard, localized cleanup tips, platform status

  - Added Offline Guard: caps offline population density on levels away from you.
    A staggered scan bins offline squads into regions by position; any region over the trigger
    is thinned to the target, so a packed hub no longer spikes the count when it comes online.
    Commanders and protected squads are never removed, so every squad survives.
  - Added Offline Guard MCM tab: toggle, cull trigger, cull target, task protection, scan tick.
    Independent of the online guard. Target down to 0 strips a region to lone commanders.
  - Added dynamic checking of xlibs and xray-monolith/AOEngine versions with a compatibility verdict.
  - An outdated xlibs no longer crashes AlifeGuard on load. The dependency check now shows the update-xlibs message instead of a raw script error from the MCM platform footer.
  - Added Russian localization for the PDA cleanup tips and the MCM reset confirmation.

1.2.7
  Summary: AOEngine compatibility, fewer engine warnings, MCM reset moved

  - Added AOEngine v0.55+ support.
  - Fixed a burst of "trying to use a destroyed object" warnings logged when a creature despawns during a cleanup cycle.
  - Moved the Reset button to the bottom of the Development tab in MCM.

1.2.6
  Summary: MCM reset crash fix, reset warning

  - Reset to defaults no longer crashes on click on certain executables
  - Added warning above reset button to save or discard pending MCM changes first.

1.2.5
  Summary: Task giver protection, crash hardening, MCM tab restructure, Reset button, notification sound, button cleanup

  Protection
    - Task givers no longer released by cleanup (no more "Mission Failed" on PDA Taskboard tasks).
      Covers PDA Taskboard task members via xlibs squad-members iteration.
      Covers orphan NPCs that are active task givers via xcreature.is_task_giver.
    - Crash hardening around stale squad references and recycled server-entity ids during release.

  Notifications
    - PDA cleanup messages now show 3 lore-flavoured Zone-as-actor lines.

  MCM
    - MCM now has three tabs: Online Guard (entity limits, protection), Smart Sanitizer, Development.
      Reset to defaults button on Development tab restores all settings to factory state in one click.
      Migration path for the restructure: old keys orphan in MCM storage but no longer apply.
    - Added Notification sound toggle on Online Guard for a brief ambient cue when cleanup fires.
    - Removed Show status, Delete common, Delete all squads buttons (cycles run automatically).
    - Removed Sanitize now, Force cleanup buttons (periodic cycles handle these).

  Compatibility
    - xlibs 1.7.1 dependency (xsquad task-giver iteration, xsound one-shot play).

1.2.0
  Summary: Smart Sanitizer clamps corrupted respawn counters on smart terrains. Prevents save crashes, starvations and infinite spawn loops or spawn caused by spawner and despawner mods.
  Core:
    Added: Smart Sanitizer. Clamps negative or non-numeric values in smart.already_spawned[k] counters. Runs once on game load after STATE_Read but before the alife pump, and every 300 seconds during play. Pure Lua table walk over SIMBOARD.smarts. Sub-millisecond on 50-200 smarts.
    Added: Post-load sanitize via actor_on_reinit. Cleans counters restored from save before try_respawn reads them. Runs before the 65534-objects-per-update boot burst would feed corrupted counters into the respawn loop.
    Fixed: Save crash from negative already_spawned counter. The packet writer at smart_terrain.script:955 casts to unsigned 8-bit. Negative values produced CTD. Sanitizer clamps to 0 before next save.
    Fixed: Infinite respawn loop from negative already_spawned counter. The respawn gate at smart_terrain.script:1696 reads max > num. Negative num made the comparison always true. Sanitizer clamps to 0.
  MCM:
    Added: Smart Sanitizer subsection on the Development tab. Toggle (default on), interval slider (60 to 1800 seconds, default 300), and immediate-sanitize diagnostic button.
  Localization:
    Added: 7 EN + 7 RU strings for the Smart Sanitizer subsection.

1.1.1
  Core:
    Changed: population scan uses xcreature.online_iter() instead of game_objects_iter (no longer crashes without Demonized exes)
  Compatibility:
    Removed: modded exes requirement. Works with vanilla Anomaly 1.5.3, Demonized, Demonized MT, AOEngine. Tested with GAMMA, EFP, Zona.

1.1.0
  Summary: Squad-aware culling, round-robin fairness, hysteresis, 4-tier priority, structured tracing

  Core:
    Changed: culling redesigned around squads, not individual entities
    Changed: entities grouped by squad, non-commanders thinned first, commanders last
    Changed: removals distributed evenly across factions and mutant types via round-robin
    Changed: 4-tier priority: unscripted members -> scripted members -> unscripted commanders -> scripted commanders
    Added: hysteresis buffer separates trigger threshold from cull target (default: trigger 80, cull to 70)
    Added: scripted squads (AlifePlus, warfare, Guards Spawner) deprioritized across both member and commander tiers

  Protection:
    Changed: protection unified at squad level via xsquad.is_protected (story, trader, task giver, companion, bounty/hostage)
    Changed: duplicate per-NPC bounty/hostage scan removed, covered by squad-level is_task_target
    Added: companion squads protected (previously only individual companion NPCs caught)
    Added: positive-only TTL cache on squad protection (120s, no false negatives, cleared on config change)
    Fixed: named NPCs as non-commander squad members now caught by per-member is_unscriptable fallback

  Performance:
    Changed: squad-level checks replace per-NPC scans, fewer bridge calls per entity
    Changed: uncached per-entity task_giver O(t) scan eliminated, replaced by cached squad-level check

  MCM:
    Changed: two-tab layout (General + Development)
    Changed: log level dropdown (ERROR/WARN/INFO/DEBUG) replaces debug_log toggle
    Changed: diagnostics and population reset moved to Development tab
    Added: hysteresis buffer slider (0-50, step 5, default 10)
    Added: per-squad culling toggle (default on, disabling reverts to v1.0 flat behavior)
    Added: round-robin fairness toggle (default on, disabling allows one faction to lose everything first)

  Internal:
    Added: xtrace IDs per cycle for structured log correlation
    Added: per-phase timing in log output (collect, queue build, release spread)
    Changed: log format standardized to [PHASE] [tid=N] key=value [Xms]

